{"bill":{"bill_id":1681249,"change_hash":"9afd5c8a42f1c233f2e07f046125d829","session_id":2019,"session":{"session_id":2019,"state_id":11,"year_start":2023,"year_end":2023,"prefile":0,"sine_die":0,"prior":0,"special":0,"session_tag":"Regular Session","session_title":"2023 Regular Session","session_name":"2023 Regular Session"},"url":"https:\/\/legiscan.com\/HI\/bill\/HB1336\/2023","state_link":"https:\/\/www.capitol.hawaii.gov\/session\/measure_indiv.aspx?billtype=HB&billnumber=1336&year=2023","completed":0,"status":1,"status_date":"2023-01-25","progress":[{"date":"2023-01-25","event":1},{"date":"2023-01-30","event":9},{"date":"2023-02-14","event":10},{"date":"2023-02-14","event":9}],"state":"HI","state_id":11,"bill_number":"HB1336","bill_type":"B","bill_type_id":"1","body":"H","body_id":31,"current_body":"H","current_body_id":31,"title":"Relating To Criminal Justice Reform.","description":"Part I: Authorizes officers to issue citations in lieu of making certain arrests. Authorizes a forty-eight hour grace period after a missed initial court appearance. Part II: Establishes a rebuttable presumption that a defendant is entitled to pretrial release. Requires the prosecution to prove by a preponderance of the evidence that release of a defendant would be inappropriate, based on certain specified criteria. Requires that bail be set in an amount that the defendant can afford, under certain circumstances. Prohibits the denial of pretrial release based solely upon certain factors, such as testing positive for drug use. Requires automatic issuance of no-contact orders in assaultive cases. Requires the prosecution, when seeking to revoke pretrial release, to prove by a preponderance of the evidence, based on certain specified criteria. Requires the court to enter certain findings into the record. Part III: Provides that a request that the defendant be ordered to undergo a substance abuse assessment may be made any time before trial. Prohibits the arrest of a probationer or parolee, or the revocation of probation or parole, solely due to the person having tested positive for drug use. Effective 6\/30\/3000. (HD1)","pending_committee_id":4406,"committee":{"committee_id":4406,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":31,"name":"Judiciary & Hawaiian Affairs"},"referrals":[{"date":"2023-01-30","committee_id":4409,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":31,"name":"Corrections, Military, & Veterans"},{"date":"2023-02-14","committee_id":4406,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":31,"name":"Judiciary & Hawaiian Affairs"}],"history":[{"date":"2023-01-25","action":"Introduced and Pass First Reading.","chamber":"H","chamber_id":31,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-01-30","action":"Referred to CMV, JHA, referral sheet 3","chamber":"H","chamber_id":31,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-01-31","action":"Bill scheduled to be heard by CMV on Friday, 02-03-23 9:00AM in House conference room 430 VIA VIDEOCONFERENCE.","chamber":"H","chamber_id":31,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-02-03","action":"The committee on CMV recommend that the measure be PASSED, WITH AMENDMENTS. The votes were as follows: 8 Ayes: Representative(s) Hashem, Chun, Ganaden, Ichiyama, Poepoe; Ayes with reservations: Representative(s) Morikawa, Takayama, Souza; Noes: none; and Excused: none.","chamber":"H","chamber_id":31,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-02-14","action":"Reported from CMV (Stand. Com. Rep. No. 360) as amended in HD 1, recommending passage on Second Reading and referral to JHA.","chamber":"H","chamber_id":31,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-02-14","action":"Passed Second Reading as amended in HD 1 and referred to the committee(s) on JHA with Representative(s) Matsumoto, Souza, Tam voting aye with reservations; Representative(s) Alcos, Garcia, Gates, Holt, Pierick, Quinlan, Ward voting no (7) and Representative(s) Kitagawa excused (1).","chamber":"H","chamber_id":31,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-02-24","action":"Bill scheduled to be heard by JHA on Tuesday, 02-28-23 2:00PM in House conference room 325 VIA VIDEOCONFERENCE.","cha